result.execSummary:
The defendant Judale Deshawn Malone Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Court set restitution at $1,265.00 to be paid to Angel V. Restitution to be paid FIRST before costs, fees and surcharges. Bail on deposit to be applied to the restitution amount. 
Court ordered a restitution hearing date be set to determine the remaining amount of restitution on October 23, 2015.

Pay all costs, fees, surcharges and restitution. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment. Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge (unless previously paid). Court costs, fees, surcharges and restitution be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/earnings.
Concurrent with: concurrent with case 15CF3002, with credit for 88 days time served.

Original Transcript (27 pages) commencing 09/21/2015 SENTENCING HEARING received and filed.

Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court, defendant Judale Deshawn Malone not in court, in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder on behalf of Michael Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for restitution hearing. State has no additional information regarding restitution as requested at the last court date. Court will not order restitution for this specific claim. All restitution previously ordered remain the same. Court took no further action.

Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court, defendant Judale Deshawn Malone not in court, in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
Case set for restitution hearing. State requested an adjournment to allow the victim to be present in court. Court granted State's request. Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Restitution hearing scheduled for November 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Judale Deshawn Malone in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Judale Deshawn Malone in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Deputy court clerk ccp.
NO COURT FILE IN COURT. Case set for plea hearing. Parties have reached a resolution. State placed negotiations on the record. Plea hearing proceeded. 

As to COUNT 1-
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty.  Judgment of conviction entered.
  
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess any gun or other firearms. 
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended, and may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored.  

Court advised defendant if he is not a citizen of the United States of America, that upon a plea of guilty or no contest for this offense, he could be deported, excluded from admission to his country, or denied naturalization under federal law.  
Court advised that the defendant will have to provide a DNA sample, to the Wisconsin State Crime Laboratory for DNA testing and pay a DNA surcharge.

Parties requested an adjourned sentencing date. Court granted joint request. 
Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into custody. 
Case adjourned to Branch 25.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 21, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
